    "This nearest-agent exclusion avoids redundant assignments and induces implicit coordination among herders without communication.",
    "Formally, a target T i is admissible for H j if the following condition is satisfied:∥T i -H j ∥ 2 < ∥T i -H a ∥ 2 for all j ̸ = a.",
    "(14)Among the admissible set of targets, the herder selects the one that is the farthest from the goal, identified with the origin, so as to reduce the worst-case distance to Ω G and promote global progress.",
    "If no admissible target is available, the herder moves at a speed v H toward the boundary of the goal region and re-engages as soon as a valid assignment arises.",
    "This rule is local and scalable, accommodates the lack of target cohesion, and provides structured role allocation while keeping the low-level controller unchanged across varying populations sizes."
